<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                    <head>No. 476.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rives</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Pendleton</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-10-20"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 20,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 371.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 675, of the 4th instant,
                        stating that the assessment of a communal income tax on Mr. S. K. Honey has
                        been discontinued and that the amounts already paid are to be refunded, has
                        been received and read with satisfaction.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">G. L. Rives</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                        Secretary.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>